==English==

===Etymology===
Hebrew אבינר (Abner), meaning "father of [or is a] light". From אָב (av = 'father') + נור (nur = 'light'). Cf. Eleanor.

===Proper noun===
'''Abner'''

# (''Bible'') [[Cousin]] of [[Saul]] in the [[Old Testament]].
# A male [given name]].

